This folder contains the JAR file for running the Fact Checking demo as propose in:

1) Kashyap Popat, Subhabrata Mukherjee, Jannik Strötgen and Gerhard Weikum.
   Where the Truth Lies: Explaining the Credibility of Emerging Claims on the Web and Social Media
   Proc. of the 26th International Conference on World Wide Web Companion, WWW 2017.

2) Kashyap Popat, Subhabrata Mukherjee, Jannik Strötgen and Gerhard Weikum. 
   CredEye: A Credibility Lens for Analyzing and Explaining Misinformation. 
   Proc. of the 2018 Web Conference (Demo), WWW 2018.


To run the JAR file, please follow the below instructions:

Step-1: 
		Prepare "config.properties" file. This contains all the required parameters to run the JAR file.
		The default values should be sufficient to run the code excpet the "bingAccountKey" parameter.
		Please subscribe to Bing Search API access (https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/services/cognitive-services/bing-web-search-api/)
   
Step-2: 
		(Only if you want to run the code for multiple claims!) 
		Prepare the input file in the tab seperated format (sample file: claim.tsv)
		<claim_id>\t<claim_text>
   
Step-3:
		Run the JAR file. It provides two configurations:
		1) Single claim
		
		java -jar FactCheck.jar -c <claim_text> -o <op_file_path> -p <properties_file_path>
		
		Example: java -jar FactCheck.jar -c "The use of solar panels drains the sun of energy" -o ./trial.json -p ./config.properties
		
		2) Multiple claims
		
		java -jar FactCheck.jar -cb <path_to_input_file> -ob <op_folder_path> -p <properties_file_path>
		
		Example: java -jar FactCheck.jar -cb ./claim.tsv -ob ./op_fold/ -p ./config.properties
		
		
		
The code outputs a JSON file per claim. The format of the output file is as following:

{
	"False": <prob_claim_being_false>,
	"True": <prob_claim_being_true>,
	"evidence":[
		{
			"snippet": <evidence_snippet_marked_with_html_tags_to_highlight_important_features>,
			"rej_prob": <stance_rejection_porobability>,
			"web_source": <domain_of_article>,
			"web_source_rel": <relaibility_score_of_web_source>,
			"cred_opinion": <credibility_score_according_to_this_article>,
			"url": <article_url>,
			"no_highlighted": <number_of_highlighted_features>
		},
		{
			....
		},
		{
			....
		}
	]
}

